msgid "wizard hat"
msgstr "wizard hat"

#: ../../W/wizard-hat.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../W/wizard-hat.rst:9
msgid ""
"[also, after Terry Pratchett, pointy hat] Notional headgear worn by whoever "
"is the :ref:`wizard` in a particular context. The implication is that it's a"
" transferable role. \"Talk to Alice, she's wearing the TCP/IP wizard hat "
"while Bob is on vacation.\" This metaphor is sufficiently live that one may "
"actually see hackers miming the act of putting on, taking off, or "
"transferring a phantom hat. See also :ref:`pointy-hat`\\, compare "
":ref:`patch-pumpkin`\\."
msgstr ""
"[Terry Pratchettにちなんで、pointy hatとも] 特定の文脈で\\ :ref:`wizard`\\ "
"である者が誰であれ被る、観念上の頭飾り。それが移譲可能な役割であることを含意する。「Aliceに話せ。Bobが休暇中の間、彼女がTCP/IPのwizard"
" hatを被っている」。この比喩は十分に生きているので、ハッカーが幻の帽子を被ったり、脱いだり、移したりする仕草を実際に演じるのを見ることがある。\\ "
":ref:`pointy-hat`\\ も参照。\\ :ref:`patch-pumpkin`\\ と比較せよ。"
